I am building a semi-professional stock analysis application called Stock2Vec.
It applies Word2Vec-style embedding training to stock price co-movement data
to discover behavioural relationships between stocks across multiple markets.

I have a complete functional specification, system architecture, and design
principles. Implement everything faithfully across multiple tasks.
Do not add features not specified.
Do not use PyTorch, TensorFlow, or any deep learning framework.
All model training must use numpy only.
Wait for my confirmation before starting each new task.
Do not proceed to the next task until I explicitly say to continue.

