SECTION 1 — CORE CONCEPT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Each trading day is treated as a sentence.
Each stock that moves meaningfully on that day is a word.
Stocks that co-move frequently end up with similar embedding vectors.
Cosine similarity between vectors measures behavioural similarity.
No labels, sector data, or human annotation used at any point.

The training loop is standard Word2Vec skip-gram in numpy:

  h      = W1[center_idx]
  scores = h @ W2
  probs  = softmax(scores)
  loss   = -log(probs[target_idx] + 1e-9)

  dscores = probs.copy()
  dscores[target_idx] -= 1        # CRITICAL: -= 1 never = -1
                                  # = -1 causes silent divergence

  dW2 = np.outer(h, dscores)
  dh  = W2 @ dscores
  dW2 = np.clip(dW2, -1.0, 1.0)
  dh  = np.clip(dh,  -1.0, 1.0)
  W2             -= lr * dW2
  W1[center_idx] -= lr * dh

W1 is kept after training as the embedding table.
W2 is discarded after training.
Loss is computed for monitoring only.
Loss value never appears in weight update calculations.

