The system trains four independent models.
Each model is self-contained with its own vocab weights and metadata.

MODEL 1 — US
  vocab:
    S&P 500 components scraped from Wikipedia on each full retrain
    NASDAQ 100 components scraped from Wikipedia on each full retrain
    US Tier A anchor ETFs 44 instruments defined in Section 4
    approximately 550 unique instruments after dedup
  anchors:
    US Tier A ETFs included in vocab and training pairs
    define the coordinate system of the embedding space
  returns:    daily log returns
  purpose:    primary US market model richest embeddings

MODEL 2 — NZX
  vocab:
    all NZX listed stocks approximately 180 tickers .NZ suffix
    hardcoded list in universe.yaml NZX changes slowly
    no anchors stocks only
    download all attempt keep those with sufficient history
    typically 120-150 successfully download log all failures
  returns:    daily log returns NZ session
  purpose:    within-NZ cluster discovery only
              no cross-market claims made by this model
  note:
    US Tier A ETFs NOT used in this model
    daily NZX and US ETF returns correspond to different sessions
    timezone misalignment makes daily co-movement unreliable
    cross-market analysis handled exclusively by Global model

MODEL 3 — ASX
  vocab:
    ASX 300 components scraped from Wikipedia on each full retrain
    approximately 300 stocks .AX suffix
    ASX sector anchor ETFs defined in Section 4
    commodity and FX anchors defined in Section 4
  anchors:
    ASX sector ETFs trade in same timezone as ASX stocks
    reliable co-movement signal
    US Tier A ETFs NOT used same timezone reason as NZX
  returns:    daily log returns AU session
  purpose:    within-AU cluster discovery and ASX factor exposures

MODEL 4 — GLOBAL
  vocab:
    union of all stocks from US plus NZX plus ASX models
    US Tier A anchor ETFs same 44 instruments as US model
    approximately 1030 unique instruments total
  anchors:
    US Tier A ETFs work here because weekly returns eliminate
    the timezone problem all markets reflect same macro week
  returns:
    weekly log returns
    prices.resample("W-FRI").last() then log returns
    W-FRI anchors week end to Friday consistent across markets
  purpose:
    cross-market analysis — the ONLY model for cross-market queries
    NZX and ASX stocks get positions relative to US anchors
    via weekly co-movement
  training order:
    always trains last depends on data from US NZX ASX

TIMEZONE RATIONALE:
  Monday NZX session corresponds to US Sunday no US trading
  Daily co-movement between NZX/ASX and US instruments
  compares returns from different actual trading sessions
  Weekly returns solve this both markets reflect same macro week
  US Tier A ETFs used ONLY in US model and Global model

