━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

DATA SOURCE: yfinance only. No paid sources.

DOWNLOAD:
  batch size:           100 tickers per yfinance call
  retry attempts:       3
  retry wait:           5 seconds between attempts
  rate limit:           1 second pause between batches
  cache format:         parquet
  cache location:       data/raw/{market}/prices.parquet
  incremental:          fetch only since get_last_date() result
  download_meta.json:
    last_downloaded_date ticker_count failed_tickers
    anomalies_detected
  on failure:           log ticker continue never crash

CLEANING:
  forward fill:         maximum 5 consecutive missing days
  drop ticker if:       fewer than 80 percent trading days have data
                        average price below 1.00
                        entire series is NaN
  anomaly detection:    single day absolute return > 25 percent
                        log to data/quality/anomaly_log.csv
                        do not remove — user decides via dashboard

RETURNS:
  daily:                np.log(prices / prices.shift(1)).dropna()
  weekly global only:   prices.resample("W-FRI").last() then log

THRESHOLD:
  formula:              threshold_multiplier * mean(std per stock)
  recomputed each run   stored in metadata.json

PAIR GENERATION:
  up bucket:            return > threshold
  down bucket:          return < negative threshold
  bidirectional:        (A,B) and (B,A) both added
  cap:                  max_pairs_per_day random sample if exceeded
  output:               list of (center_idx, target_idx) int tuples

