TWO ENVIRONMENTS:

  Local development:
    developer laptop
    host 127.0.0.1 port 8050
    STOCK2VEC_ENV=development
    S3_BACKUP_BUCKET empty string skips backup silently
    small scale training for validation
    git commits and pushes to GitHub

  AWS EC2 production:
    all full training runs
    dashboard accessible from anywhere
    STOCK2VEC_ENV=production
    host 0.0.0.0 nginx proxies to 8050

AWS SERVICES:

  EC2 t3.medium 2 vCPU 4GB RAM Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
    region ap-southeast-2 Sydney
    running continuously approximately $15 per month

  EBS gp3 50GB attached to EC2
    all application data persists here
    approximately $4 per month

  Elastic IP fixed public address
    free when attached to running instance

  S3 bucket stock2vec-backups
    model weight backups after each training run
    IAM instance profile with S3 read write list only
    never hardcode AWS credentials
    approximately $0.50 per month

  Security group:
    port 22 SSH your IP only
    port 443 HTTPS 0.0.0.0/0
    port 80 HTTP 0.0.0.0/0 redirects to 443
    outbound all allowed for yfinance downloads

PROCESSES ON EC2:

  nginx: system service always running
    reverse proxy 443 to 127.0.0.1:8050
    basic auth via htpasswd
    proxy_read_timeout 300s

  stock2vec-dashboard: systemd service always running
    restarts automatically on failure
    loads all four models on startup
    polls training_status.json every 5 seconds
    polls reload_signal.json every 30 seconds

  training process: spawned as detached subprocess
    progress written to training_status.json
    dashboard polls and shows progress
    reload signal written on completion
    dashboard reloads weights automatically

DATA FLOW:

  yfinance -> IncrementalDownloader -> ParquetCache
    -> StandardCleaner -> LogReturnsProcessor
    -> VolatilityThresholdStrategy -> CoMovementPairGenerator
    -> Word2VecModel via Trainer with observers
    -> ModelVersioning -> current/ pointer
    -> reload_signal.json -> ModelStore reload
    -> ModelBackup -> S3

